<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="A/B Roll" class="currentChild" href="B_Roll">A/B Roll</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In video editing, a device comprising two video sources (such as videotapes or videodiscs) and a single video recorder. The operator switches between the two input video signals by means of a <a title="digital video effects generator" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/digital_video_effects_generator">digital video effects generator</a> to add special <a title="Transition" href="../Transition">transition</a>s such as <a title="Wipe" href="../Wipe">wipe</a>s and <a title="Dissolve" href="../Dissolve">dissolve</a>s between different scenes. Digital video editing software such as Adobe Premiere also allows a type of A/B roll editing or transitioning between different video signals. 
</p>
